Aim :- To interface an HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor with STM32 and control an LED based on distance
Apparatus :- STM32 Nucleo-F446RE Board ; HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor ; Jumper Wires ; USB Cable; STM32CubeIDE; STM32CubeMX
Theory :- The HC-SR04 sensor is used to measure distance using ultasonic waves. It sends a signal(TRIG) and receives it back(ECHO).
The time taken by the signal to return is used to calculate distance.
STM32 reads this time and calculates distance using:
   Distance =(Soeed*Time)/2
If the object is close,LED turns ON.If far,LED turns OFF.
